sub_title: Material Chemist,  Project Associate (Seeking Job in Related Field)
summary:
I have experience in the interdisciplinary area of Inorganic Materials. My research work was focussed on the preparation of Nano-composites for humidity sensor application. I also worked in the area of chemical sensor, heavy metal ion sensors and quantum cluster based solar cell. I have explored multiple aspects involving electrospinning of nanofibers and solar cell application using nanoclusters. 
Capable of performing the synthesis of nanomaterials by various synthesis techniques. Synthesis of metal oxide and semiconductor based nanomaterials (Solid-State Reaction, Sol-gel method, Citrate method, Precipitation method, hydrothermal method).
Knowledge in device fabrication processes for sensor (Humidity and gas) application. Experienced in fabrication of solar cells and modules.
Knowledge in material characterization (UV-Spectroscopy, TG-DTA ,  FT-IR, FT-Raman, Powder X-Ray Diffraction, SEM/EDAX , TEM and BET). 
Hands-on experience in Ultra Centrifuge; FT-IR Spectroscopy (Perkin Elmer); UV-Vis Spectroscopy; Cyclic Voltammetry (CH604C); Powder X-Ray Diffraction; TG-DTA (Perkin Elmer); Chemical Vapour Deposition; Keithley Picoammeter; Spray pyrolysis deposition system; Spin Coating; Electro-spinning Unit; Solar Simulator; Electrochemical work station for Impedance measurements and Incident Photo conversion efficiency system. 
I have a profound knowledge to write research articles and project proposal in materials. Ability to work independently and interact with multidisciplinary chemists and external collaborators and ability to supervise BS/MS/Ph.D chemists.
Willing to learn new field of work in chemistry and do my best.
